HEADWORD: Irreprovable
<hw>Ir`re*prov"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Incapable of
being justly reproved; irreproachable; blameless; upright.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Ir`re*prov"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Ir`re*prov"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irreptitious</ent>⟦br⟧
